#Approach:

Approach (Hinglish) – Kth Missing Positive Number (Binary Search)

Is question mein hume kth missing positive number find karna hai
given sorted strictly increasing array se.

Brute force mein hum ek-ek missing number count kar sakte hain,
lekin yaha binary search se aur efficient kaam ho jata hai.

Key Idea:
Agar array perfect hoti without any missing numbers,
to index 0 par value 1 honi chahiye,
index 1 par value 2,
index 2 par value 3, and so on.

Matlab expected value at index mid = mid + 1

Toh kisi bhi index mid par missing numbers count hoga:
missing = arr[mid] - (mid + 1)

Example:
arr = [2,3,4,7,11]

Index 0 -> expected = 1, actual = 2
missing = 2 - 1 = 1

Index 3 -> expected = 4, actual = 7
missing = 7 - 4 = 3

Iska matlab index 3 tak total 3 numbers missing hain.

Binary Search Idea:
Hume first aisa index chahiye jahan missing count >= k ho jaye.
Us point ke just pehle tak missing count k se chhota hoga.

Agar missing < k
-> Abhi tak k missing numbers complete nahi hue
-> right side jao

Agar missing >= k
-> Ho sakta hai answer left side mein ho
-> left side jao

Why answer = low + k ?
Binary search ke end par low wo position hoti hai
jahan tak missing numbers ka count k ya usse zyada ho jata hai.

Us case mein kth missing number = low + k

Example:
arr = [2,3,4,7,11], k = 5

Binary search ke baad low = 4
Answer = low + k = 4 + 5 = 9

Steps:
1. low = 0, high = n - 1
2. mid calculate karo
3. missing = arr[mid] - (mid + 1)
4. Agar missing < k
   -> right side jao
   -> low = mid + 1
5. Else
   -> left side jao
   -> high = mid - 1
6. Loop ke end par answer = low + k

Time Complexity:
O(log n)

Space Complexity:
O(1)

One line intuition:
Har index par count karo ki ab tak kitne positive numbers missing hain,
aur binary search se first aisa index dhoondo jahan missing count k tak pahunch jaye.

#Code:

class Solution {
    public int findKthPositive(int[] arr, int k) {
        int low = 0;
        int high = arr.length - 1;

        while(low <= high){
            int mid = (low + high)/2;
            int missing = arr[mid] - (mid+1);

            if(missing < k){
                low = mid+1;
            }
            else{
                high = mid-1;
            }
        }
        return low + k;
        
    }
}
